      <h1 class="section-heading">Moderation Philosophy</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Moderation within the TGK Community is principled and minimal. It exists to preserve 
        the quality of dialogue and protect participants from degradation, not to suppress 
        disagreement or enforce ideological conformity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT MODERATION DOES -->
    <section class="section-block">
      <h2 class="section-heading">What Moderation Does</h2>

      <ul class="rules-list">
        <li>Prevents harassment or humiliation.</li>
        <li>Ensures replies include an appropriate Steel Man summary.</li>
        <li>Removes incoherent, malicious, or unserious contributions.</li>
        <li>Protects users from impersonation or targeted hostility.</li>
        <li>Upholds the Charter and Participation Guide in spirit and practice.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT MODERATION DOES NOT DO -->
    <section class="section-block">
      <h2 class="section-heading">What Moderation Does Not Do</h2>

      <ul class="rules-list">
        <li>Suppress reasonable disagreement.</li>
        <li>Enforce political or ideological alignment.</li>
        <li>Intervene in disputes outside TGK spaces.</li>
        <li>Censor criticism expressed in good faith.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ETHOS -->
    <section class="section-block">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Moderation Ethos</h2>
      <p>
        Moderators serve as custodians rather than authorities. Their purpose is to maintain 
        a space where serious thought can develop, where ideas are treated with rigour, and where
        users feel free to explore difficult questions without fear of ridicule.
      </p>
    </section>

